BARGAINTOWN, U. S. A., INC., et al. v. WHITMAN, DISTRICT ATTORNEY OF LEBANON COUNTY, PA., et al. No. 76. Decided June 19, 1961.

— F. Supp. —, affirmed.

David G. Bress and Leonard Braman for appellants. Anne X. Alpern, Attorney General of Pennsylvania, and Harry J. Rubin for appellees. Per Curiam.

The judgment is affirmed. McGowan v. Maryland, 366 U. S. 420, and Two Guys from Harrison-Allentown, Inc., v. McGinley, 366 U. S. 582.

Mr. Justice Douglas is of the opinion that probable jurisdiction should be noted.
